Before proceeding, it is clarified here that, although the notation used does not reveal any dependence of the time-warping function ψ(⋅) on the phenomenon characterized by x(⋅), there is nothing in the theory or method presented here that prohibits such dependence, with one exception that is explained in Section 6. The only limitation on the nature of such dependence is that, to be physically viable, the dependence must (according to generally—but not unanimously—accepted principles of cosmology) be causal, meaning that the dependence ψt=ψtxv:v<t\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
