				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ \psi (t)=\psi \left(t;\left\{x(v):v<t\right\}\right) $$\end{document} is possible, but v in this expression cannot be allowed to exceed t. This clarification can be summarized as follow:
The manner in which present cyclicity of a phenomenon departs from being regular can depend on past behavior of the phenomenon.

