As inferred in preceding sections, de-warping or warping compensation may not be possible for severe cases of time warping. In addition, there also are types of irregular cyclicity that are not due to time warping or cannot be modeled as time-warped regular cyclicity. In some such cases, it is possible that none of the methods described in this and preceding sections would be able to adequately reduce the irregularity of cyclicity. To illustrate, the following baseline signal model is considered:yt=xψt=∑nqnψt−nTo\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
