The pace-irregular model Eq. 37a, and associated rotation-angle model (with unwrapped angle θ), as Eq. 37b shall be called, is useful for random vibrations y(t) from rotating machinery with a fault point in some rotating component. In this model, the pulses or bursts {qn(t)} represent the machine structure’s vibration response (typically damped ringing), which is modeled as independent of the times of occurrence of the causative impulsive shocks from the rotating fault. The advancing rotation angle can be expressed in terms of instantaneous frequency as follows:θt=∫totωudu+θto.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
