Equality in Eq. 43 might well suffice when the optimum (most efficient) set of basis functions, which is the smallest set that spans the space of all possible time-warping or warp-compensating functions, is used. For example, for the space defined by a maximum possible time-bandwidth product (e.g., not exceeding Bψ−1T\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
